answers.body_markdown:
`MatchPhrasePrefix` query **must** also specify a field to target. For example

```c#
var searchResponse2 = client.Search&lt;dynamic&gt;(s =&gt; s
	.AllTypes()
	.AllIndices()
	.IgnoreUnavailable()
	.Size(100)
	.From(0)
	.Query(q =&gt; q
		.Bool(b =&gt; b
			.Must(m =&gt; m
				.MatchPhrasePrefix(c =&gt; c
					.Field(&quot;some_field&quot;) // &lt;-- target the &quot;some_field&quot; field
					.Query(&quot;query&quot;)
				)
			)
		)
	)
);
```

which results in the query

    POST /_search
    {
      &quot;from&quot;: 0,
      &quot;query&quot;: {
        &quot;bool&quot;: {
          &quot;must&quot;: [
            {
              &quot;match_phrase_prefix&quot;: {
                &quot;some_field&quot;: {
                  &quot;query&quot;: &quot;query&quot;
                }
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      &quot;size&quot;: 100
    }

Without specifying the field, the query is considered _conditionless_ in the client, and will be omitted from the response. There&#39;s [an issue](https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch-net/issues/4050) to discuss whether _conditionless_ queries should be removed in the next major version.

